                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On August 23, 1954, in Washington, representatives of the Governments of the
                    United States and Pakistan signed an agreement extending emergency assistance by
                    the United States to help relieve the effects of a flood disaster in East
                    Pakistan. (Press release, Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                    September 6, 1954, page 338) The text of the agreement for Emergency Flood
                    Relief Assistance is printed in 5 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 2)
                    1779.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
